# P6-001: plink_pca — Principal Component Analysis

## Overview

`plink_pca(path)` computes per-sample principal component scores via
randomized SVD (Halko et al. 2011), matching plink2's `--pca approx`
algorithm. Uses Eigen3 (header-only) for linear algebra — no LAPACK
dependency.

**Workflow frequency**: Extremely common. PCA is used in virtually every
GWAS pipeline for population stratification correction. The output (PC
scores) feeds directly into `plink_glm` as covariates.

**Justification**: Cannot be expressed in SQL on existing function output.
Requires streaming the full genotype matrix with normalization and matrix
decomposition — a dedicated function with pgenlib fast-paths is the only
viable approach at biobank scale.

---

## Function Signature

```sql
plink_pca(path VARCHAR,
          -- Output control (uses 'mode' for consistency with plink_missing)
          mode := 'samples',       -- 'samples' | 'pcs' | 'both'
          n_pcs := 10,             -- number of principal components
          -- Standard filters
          samples := NULL,         -- LIST(VARCHAR) or LIST(INTEGER)
          region := NULL,          -- VARCHAR 'chr:start-end'
          variants := NULL,        -- LIST(VARCHAR) or LIST(INTEGER)
          af_range := NULL,        -- STRUCT{min, max}
          ac_range := NULL,        -- STRUCT{min, max}
          -- Companion file overrides
          pvar := NULL,            -- VARCHAR
          psam := NULL             -- VARCHAR
)
```

---

## Output Schemas

### `mode := 'samples'` (default)

One row per sample. Matches plink2's `.eigenvec` output. Analogous to
`plink_missing` `mode := 'variant'` / `mode := 'sample'`.

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| FID | VARCHAR | Family ID (from .psam, may be absent) |
| IID | VARCHAR | Individual ID |
| PC1 | DOUBLE | First principal component score |
| PC2 | DOUBLE | Second principal component score |
| ... | ... | ... |
| PCk | DOUBLE | k-th principal component score |

Column count depends on `n_pcs`. Supports projection pushdown — if only
PC1 and PC2 are selected, eigendecomposition still computes all requested
PCs (unavoidable) but only the projected columns are emitted.

### `mode := 'pcs'`

One row per principal component. Matches plink2's `.eigenval` output.

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| PC | INTEGER | Principal component number (1-based) |
| EIGENVALUE | DOUBLE | Eigenvalue (variance explained by this PC) |
| VARIANCE_PROPORTION | DOUBLE | Proportion of total variance explained |
| CUMULATIVE_VARIANCE | DOUBLE | Cumulative proportion of variance explained |

### `mode := 'both'`

Single-row table containing the full decomposition as nested structures.
Lower implementation priority — can be deferred if the other two modes
cover the primary use cases.

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| EIGENVEC | STRUCT(FID VARCHAR, IID VARCHAR, PC1 DOUBLE, ...)[] | Array of per-sample PC scores |
| EIGENVAL | DOUBLE[] | Array of eigenvalues |

